{
  "texts": [
    "We read the abstracts of the articles whose titles seemed relevant to our research topic and tried to apply the inclusion and exclusion criteria to select the relevant articles.",
    "We quickly realised that selection based on title and abstract was not working well.",
    "This is because the presence of the key search terms (for example, \"ethics\" AND \"AI\" AND \"developer\") was rather common and did not imply that the paper would include the practitioner's perspective on ethics in AI.",
    "We found ourselves having to scan through full texts to judge the relevance to our research question (RQ).",
    "Despite the effort involved, the return on investment was very low, for example, for every hundred papers read, we found only one or two relevant papers, i.e., those that included the AI practitioners' views on ethics in AI."
  ]
}